    {
      "id": "a1ecf93720b4f54bc1ebd3c787a27a915d6a186c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 428,
        "name": "Wang Shilong",
        "email": "wangshilong1991@gmail.com",
        "username": "wangshilong",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2021-01-19 23:48:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> > Just one question in the Gerrit Janitor testing at\n > > https://testing-archive.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/13692/testresults/sanity-quota-ldiskfs-DNE-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/sanity-quota.suite_log.oleg246-client.log\n > > under test 3a, I see:\n > > Block grace time: 20s; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Block grace time: 1w; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Block grace time: 1w; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Write before timer goes off\n > > running as uid/gid/euid/egid 60000/60000/60000/60000, groups:\n > > [dd] [if=/dev/zero] [of=/mnt/lustre/d3a.sanity-quota/f3a.sanity-quota-0]\n > > [bs=1K] [count=10] [seek=5120]\n > > 10+0 records in\n > > 10+0 records out\n > > 10240 bytes (10 kB) copied, 0.00693563 s, 1.5 MB/s\n > > Grace time is 19s\n > >\n > > It looks like the grace time is 20 second and then, once in\n > > wait_grace_time() the grace time is reported at 19 seconds.\n > \n > I noticed this also in the tests that I reviewed.  I think this is\n > caused by the grace time \"counting down\" from when the quota was\n > first exceeded until it expires and the hard limit is enforced.\n > \n > > If this patch needs to be rebased/modified, please add\n > > \"testlist=sanity-quota\" to the test parameters line so\n > sanity-quota\n > > is run.\n > \n > Yes, it definitely make sense that a patch modifying sanity-quota\n > should be *running* sanity-quota.  While the Janitor test runs are\n > good, they have a different environment and may see different\n > problems.  We've hit many cases of \"trivial\" patches landing and\n > then breaking testing, so better to do the correct testing.\n\nI thought trivial tested sanity-quota before, but something changed, and i was wrong..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "7c1a7f5de34cdb0a2b261ab51f74ebad17a9d9c6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 428,
        "name": "Wang Shilong",
        "email": "wangshilong1991@gmail.com",
        "username": "wangshilong",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2021-01-19 23:52:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> > Just one question in the Gerrit Janitor testing at\n > > https://testing-archive.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/13692/testresults/sanity-quota-ldiskfs-DNE-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/sanity-quota.suite_log.oleg246-client.log\n > > under test 3a, I see:\n > > Block grace time: 20s; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Block grace time: 1w; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Block grace time: 1w; Inode grace time: 1w\n > > Write before timer goes off\n > > running as uid/gid/euid/egid 60000/60000/60000/60000, groups:\n > > [dd] [if=/dev/zero] [of=/mnt/lustre/d3a.sanity-quota/f3a.sanity-quota-0]\n > > [bs=1K] [count=10] [seek=5120]\n > > 10+0 records in\n > > 10+0 records out\n > > 10240 bytes (10 kB) copied, 0.00693563 s, 1.5 MB/s\n > > Grace time is 19s\n > >\n > > It looks like the grace time is 20 second and then, once in\n > > wait_grace_time() the grace time is reported at 19 seconds.\n > \n > I noticed this also in the tests that I reviewed.  I think this is\n > caused by the grace time \"counting down\" from when the quota was\n > first exceeded until it expires and the hard limit is enforced.\n\nYes, i agreed with Andreas's point here.\n\n > \n > > If this patch needs to be rebased/modified, please add\n > > \"testlist=sanity-quota\" to the test parameters line so\n > sanity-quota\n > > is run.\n > \n > Yes, it definitely make sense that a patch modifying sanity-quota\n > should be *running* sanity-quota.  While the Janitor test runs are\n > good, they have a different environment and may see different\n > problems.  We've hit many cases of \"trivial\" patches landing and\n > then breaking testing, so better to do the correct testing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
